
======================================== How to use ===============================

STEP_01:
========
-Create A Folder with "Project Name"
-Create file name "SASS/custom.scss" and 
-Create more files, start with "_" for exmaple: _utilites.scss 
-Import the files with code @import "_utilities" to custom.scss;

STEP_02:
========
-Create file index.html with bs5 boiler-plate and include automatic generated css/custom.css 

STEP_03:
========
--Click watch scss on VS-CODE




================================ VS Code Extention ==================================

01. live server-by ritwik dey

=======02. live saas compiler -by Glnn Marks ================
-----------STEP: 01
**After installion, it will show Watch Sass bottom of VS code 
** if does not show Press "ctrl+shift+P" Search Live Sass and click)
01> VS-Code: Terminal>new Terminal
02> npm install bootstrap (install latested version of bootstrap with scss files)

-----------STEP: 02
03> Create file SCSS>custom.scss And Import bootstrap Scss file (@import "../node_modules/bootstrap/scss/bootstrap.scss")
04> Output will show in Css folder (If does not show follow the below instrunction)

To save file inside css folder (if no such folder, it will create it)
--Go to VS code settings and 
--Search "live Sass"Compile"
--Click on "Edit in settings.json"
--Add below lines and save it:
  "liveSassCompile.settings.formats": [{
      "format": "compressed",
      "extensionName": ".min.css",
      "savePath": "/css"
  }]

Now Click on "Watch Sass" bottom bar of VS Code

